The paper deals with distributed algorithms and communication complexity, which are typical topics in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The Lov\'asz local lemma is a well-known tool in probabilistic combinatorics, which is relevant to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves graph theory, which is a topic in the Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
